4. SOLIDARITY ECONOMICS (RECOMMENDED, NOT REQUIRED)

   We encourage (but do not require) downstream users to:

   a) Share improvements back to the community
   b) Support the original project financially if commercially successful
   c) Prioritize cooperative economic models
   d) Consider collective ownership structures
   e) Contribute to Commons-based initiatives

   Recommended support mechanisms:
   - Open Collective: https://opencollective.com/aws-edu
   - Direct contributions to upstream project
   - In-kind support (documentation, bug fixes, testing)

5. SHARING IMPROVEMENTS (ENCOURAGED)

   While not legally required, we strongly encourage:

   a) Publishing modifications under compatible licenses
   b) Contributing improvements upstream
   c) Documenting changes and rationale
   d) Participating in community governance

